<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 3:26PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Rockingham, western Caswell and southwestern
Pittsylvania Counties and the City of Danville through 400 PM EDT...
At 326 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cascade, or near Mayfield, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Providence...
Mayfield...
and Camp Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
